article.headline: Utah Valley St. 84, Peru St. 49
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Holton Hunsaker had 21 points and five steals Monday night to help Utah Valley beat Peru State 84-49. Antoine Hosley scored 19 points and Nick Thompson had 15 points and 10 rebounds for the Wolverines (10-15). Taylor Brown added 10 points for Utah Valley. Peru State, which plays in the NAIA, never led in the game. Derrick Williams was the only player in double figures for the Bobcats, with 15 points. Utah Valley shot 48 percent and led 46-22 at the break. Peru State finished at 29 percent from the field.
